# TotalSegmentator Batch Segmentation Script

This repository contains a Python script (`run_totalseg_batch.py`) for running **[TotalSegmentator](https://github.com/wasserth/TotalSegmentator)** on multiple CT scans automatically.  
It processes each patient folder, detects the `CT_reg` image, and generates segmentation masks for the **liver**, **fat**, and **body**.

---

## 🧠 Overview

For each patient directory (e.g. `AB_1ABA009`), the script:

1. Finds the CT image in: `<PATIENT_FOLDER>/CT_reg/<something>CT_reg.nii.gz`
2. Creates an output directory:
3. Runs TotalSegmentator to generate:
- **Liver mask** – via `task="total", roi_subset=["liver"]`
- **Fat & muscle masks** – via `task="tissue_types"`
- **Body mask** – via `task="body"`

Each set of masks is saved as NIfTI files (`.nii.gz`) inside the output folder.

---

## ⚙️ Requirements

- Python ≥ 3.9  
- Conda environment (recommended)
- [PyTorch](https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally) (CPU or CUDA GPU build)
- [TotalSegmentator](https://github.com/wasserth/TotalSegmentator)

Example setup:
```bash
conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate totalseg

